_:Ne8b37f8f6e2747e8b2dadf25036471bc <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.business.gov.uk/invest-in-uk/\">Office for Investment (<abbr title=\"Office for Investment\">OfI</abbr>)</a> is the UK government’s front door for strategic, high-value investment that creates large numbers of jobs, strengthens supply chains, and reinforces key Industrial Strategy sectors.</p>\n\n<p>Strategic investors can expect personalised support to help land UK investment, and continued support to grow that investment. We offer:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>investor problem solving including planning, grids, skills, and visas</li>\n  <li>relationships spanning local, regional, and central government</li>\n  <li>expertise across sectors, asset classes, and geographic marketplaces</li>\n  <li>access to regulators and professional service partners</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"why-choose-the-uk\">Why choose the UK?</h2>\n\n<ol>\n  <li>\n    <p>Strategic framework for investors. The UK’s Industrial Strategy, backed by government and industry, identifies 8 high-potential sectors where the UK has international advantage: advanced manufacturing, clean energy, creative, defence, digital and technology, financial services, life sciences, and professional services.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Active government support to remove barriers. This includes accelerated planning and grid connections, fast tracking of critical infrastructure, and targeted regulatory reform measures. In terms of talent, the UK encourages the best and brightest while collaborating with industry to meet long-term skills requirements.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Stability in an uncertain world. The UK has strong institutional stability, rule of law, industrial depth, and a vision for long-term success.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>An open, trading economy. The UK is a strategic gateway between Europe and the <abbr title=\"United States of America\">USA</abbr>, supported by preferential access. Beneficial trade agreements also enable market diversification, scale, and future growth including: <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr>, the Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership (<abbr title=\"Comprehensive and Progressive Agreement for Trans-Pacific Partnership\">CPTPP</abbr>), Japan, South Korea, Singapore, Australia/New Zealand, and India.</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Access to finance. Supported by highly liquid markets, the UK is Europe’s leading venture capital market and startup ecosystem, with the highest number of unicorns. The London Stock Exchange adds further depth and exit options.</p>\n  </li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Office for Investment\">OfI</abbr> is part of Department for Business and Trade and combines expertise from the Department for Business and Trade, His Majesty’s Treasury, and the Prime Minister’s Office, 10 Downing Street to deliver strategic investment projects.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"groups-within-the-office-for-investment\">Groups within the Office for Investment</h2>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/office-for-investment-financial-services\">Office for Investment: Financial Services</a> is the single front door for international financial services firms wishing to set up or expand their operations in the UK.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.business.gov.uk/campaign/global-talent/\">Global Talent</a> is the cross-government lead on attracting elite talent to the UK.</p>\n\n</div>" .
